    "description": {
      "value": "\n<p><b>Type:</b> Chakra Control </p>\n<p><b>Rank:</b> 2 (Spell Level 1)</p>\n<p><b>Chakra Cost:</b> 2</p>\n\n<p><b>Learn DC:</b> 14 | <b>Successes:</b> 1</p>\n<p><b>Perform:</b> 2 | <b>Perform DC:</b> 13</p>\n\n<p><b>Components:</b> C</p>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p>You turn 3 Diminutive or Tiny paper objects per level into solid and sharp improvised weapons, which can be wielded as melee or thrown weapons with a range increment of 10 ft. The weapon's base damage is 1d3 for Diminutive objects (advanced seals, exploding tags, playing cards, etc.) and 1d4 for Tiny objects (an average size sheet of paper). Once a hardened object is no longer held by you, it returns to its previous state after one round.<br><br>This technique cannot solidify more than one Chakra-bearing object (like an exploding tag or advanced seal) among the objects it affects. If such an object is thrown and hits a creature, they are denied a Reflex save against the object, unless it is removed before it activates.</p>\n\n\n\n",
      "summary": "",
      "instructions": ""
    },
